WEBVTT

00:01.460 --> 00:03.462
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

00:22.773 --> 00:24.942
[ POP MUSIC PLAYING ]

00:31.072 --> 00:32.240
[ SIGHS ]

00:39.456 --> 00:40.749
IT'S QUITE A PLACE.

00:40.791 --> 00:42.250
HMM.

00:40.791 --> 00:42.250
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:42.292 --> 00:44.920
SHOULD HAVE SEEN IT IN THE '40s.

00:44.962 --> 00:46.922
MAN, THIS WAS THE PLACE TO BE.

00:46.964 --> 00:48.507
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:48.549 --> 00:49.591
YEAH, THEY'D HAVE SHOWS

00:49.633 --> 00:52.594
AND PROFESSIONAL SKATERS

00:49.633 --> 00:52.594
FROM ALL OVER.

00:52.636 --> 00:54.722
THAT WURLITZER...

00:54.763 --> 00:57.265
[ CHUCKLES ]

00:57.307 --> 01:00.936
...IT WOULD SHAKE THE RAFTERS.

01:00.978 --> 01:02.938
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:02.980 --> 01:05.148
WHERE IS IT, CHARLIE?

01:07.401 --> 01:09.528
I BEG YOUR PARDON.

01:09.570 --> 01:11.989
YOU WENT TO WAR IN 1942.

01:12.031 --> 01:14.992
YOU CAME HOME WITH

01:12.031 --> 01:14.992
A VERY VALUABLE PAINTING.

01:15.034 --> 01:17.661
LOOTING ART FROM THE BATTLEFIELD

01:15.034 --> 01:17.661
IS A SERIOUS CRIME.

01:17.703 --> 01:19.329
TELL ME WHERE IT IS RIGHT NOW...

01:19.371 --> 01:21.916
YOU WON'T GO TO JAIL.

01:21.957 --> 01:24.919
I NEVER LOOTED ANYTHING

01:21.957 --> 01:24.919
IN MY LIFE.

01:24.960 --> 01:28.756
AND IF ANYONE'S GOING TO JAIL,

01:24.960 --> 01:28.756
IT'S YOU...

01:28.797 --> 01:33.719
FOR WAVING THAT FAKE DIME-STORE

01:28.797 --> 01:33.719
BADGE IN FRONT OF MY FACE.

01:33.761 --> 01:36.221
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:36.263 --> 01:38.390
FAIR ENOUGH.

01:38.432 --> 01:39.892
BUT KNOW THIS --

01:39.934 --> 01:42.895
THE MAN THAT HIRED ME

01:39.934 --> 01:42.895
TO GET THAT PAINTING

01:42.937 --> 01:45.647
WILL HUNT YOU LIKE A DOG

01:42.937 --> 01:45.647
UNTIL HE GETS IT.

01:48.943 --> 01:50.569
SON OF A --

01:50.611 --> 01:52.613
[ HEART BEATING ]

01:55.616 --> 01:57.618
[ GRUNTS ]

02:02.873 --> 02:06.877
-HEY, YOU GUYS.

02:02.873 --> 02:06.877
-IS HE ALL RIGHT?

02:09.046 --> 02:11.172
'CAUSE I JUST DON'T SEE

02:11.214 --> 02:12.841
HOW I.Y.S. INSURANCE

02:11.214 --> 02:12.841
WOULD FORCE YOU OUT.

02:12.883 --> 02:14.676
I MEAN, NOBODY CLOSED MORE

02:12.883 --> 02:14.676
INVESTIGATIONS THAN YOU,

02:14.718 --> 02:16.177
-EXCEPT ME.

02:14.718 --> 02:16.177
-GENTLEMEN?

02:16.219 --> 02:18.138
UM, IRISH, NEAT, AND, UH --

02:16.219 --> 02:18.138
WHAT'LL YOU HAVE?

02:18.179 --> 02:19.890
COFFEE, THANKS.

02:19.932 --> 02:21.224
DERELICTION OF DUTIES.

02:21.266 --> 02:23.560
THEY DECIDED I WAS OBSESSED,

02:21.266 --> 02:23.560
CHASING A GHOST.

02:23.602 --> 02:26.521
AND THEY WERE RIGHT.

02:23.602 --> 02:26.521
UNTIL THIS WEEK.

02:26.563 --> 02:28.356
YOU FOUND IT?

02:26.563 --> 02:28.356
[ LATCHES CLICK ]

02:28.398 --> 02:30.025
A WOMAN IN DUSSELDORF

02:30.067 --> 02:32.569
FOUND THESE IN HER ATTIC

02:30.067 --> 02:32.569
TWO WEEKS AGO.

02:32.611 --> 02:35.072
THEY'RE LOVE LETTERS

02:32.611 --> 02:35.072
FROM A CONRAD BECKER,

02:35.114 --> 02:37.407
A NAZI INFANTRYMAN,

02:35.114 --> 02:37.407
TO THIS WOMAN'S MOTHER.

02:37.449 --> 02:41.161
IN THEM, HE REFERS TO A PAINTING

02:37.449 --> 02:41.161
HE STASHED IN HIS GEAR.

02:41.202 --> 02:42.496
HMM.

02:42.537 --> 02:44.372
THE  PAINTING.

02:44.414 --> 02:47.042
OKAY, BUT WE -- WE HAVE HEARD

02:44.414 --> 02:47.042
THESE CLAIMS BEFORE.

02:47.084 --> 02:49.294
YEAH, BUT THIS TIME

02:47.084 --> 02:49.294
THE FACTS BEAR HIM OUT.

02:49.336 --> 02:52.631
LOOK, HE WAS STATIONED

02:49.336 --> 02:52.631
AT THE FRIEDRICH-KAISER MUSEUM

02:52.673 --> 02:55.550
ON THE NIGHT OF THE BOMBING

02:52.673 --> 02:55.550
OF MAGDEBURG.

02:55.592 --> 02:58.887
HE HELPED PUT OUT THE FIRE.

02:55.592 --> 02:58.887
I  KNOW  THIS IS TRUE.

02:58.929 --> 03:02.223
HE SAVED THE LOST VAN GOGH.

03:02.265 --> 03:04.434
WHERE DOES, UH --

03:02.265 --> 03:04.434
WHERE DOES THIS TRAIL LEAD?

03:04.476 --> 03:06.478
OREGON.

03:06.520 --> 03:09.898
WHY DON'T WE, UH, SIT DOWN?

03:09.940 --> 03:11.108
GO ON.

03:11.150 --> 03:14.361
IN 1944, BECKER'S UNIT

03:11.150 --> 03:14.361
WAS SENT TO FRANCE,

03:14.402 --> 03:16.530
WHERE HE WAS KILLED

03:14.402 --> 03:16.530
BY U.S. TROOPS.

03:16.571 --> 03:18.032
AND THERE, IT SEEMS,

03:18.073 --> 03:20.534
THE PAINTING WAS TAKEN

03:18.073 --> 03:20.534
BY THIS MAN --

03:20.575 --> 03:22.494
CHARLES LAWSON.

03:22.536 --> 03:24.788
AND WHAT DOES,

03:22.536 --> 03:24.788
UH, MR. CHARLES LAWSON

03:24.830 --> 03:26.165
HAVE TO SAY ABOUT THIS?

03:26.205 --> 03:29.292
NOTHING. HE REFUSES TO TALK

03:26.205 --> 03:29.292
TO ME...OR TO ANYONE.

03:29.334 --> 03:32.295
HE WAS JUST CHECKED INTO A LOCAL

03:29.334 --> 03:32.295
HOSPITAL WITH CHEST PAINS.

03:32.337 --> 03:36.550
YOU KNOW, UH, OWEN, I'M OUT

03:32.337 --> 03:36.550
OF THE ART-RECOVERY BUSINESS.

03:36.591 --> 03:39.053
BUT YOU ARE IN THE...

03:39.094 --> 03:40.554
PEOPLE-HELPING BUSINESS,

03:39.094 --> 03:40.554
RIGHT?

03:40.595 --> 03:43.015
THE WORD IS OUT ON THIS, NATE.

03:43.057 --> 03:46.185
THE BILLIONAIRES' CLUB

03:43.057 --> 03:46.185
WANTS THIS PAINTING,

03:46.226 --> 03:48.020
AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA ASK

03:46.226 --> 03:48.020
A LOT OF QUESTIONS

03:48.062 --> 03:49.938
ABOUT HOW THEY GET IT.

03:57.320 --> 04:01.116
I THOUGHT I FOUND IT YEARS AGO

03:57.320 --> 04:01.116
IN A VAULT IN KYOTO,

04:01.158 --> 04:02.283
BUT IT WAS A FAKE.

04:02.325 --> 04:03.618
YEAH, NO.

04:02.325 --> 04:03.618
I-I CHASED IT, TOO.

04:03.660 --> 04:05.620
BUENOS AIRES, DAMASCUS, KIEV.

04:05.662 --> 04:08.289
I MEAN, IT WAS THE WHITE WHALE

04:05.662 --> 04:08.289
OF ART-THEFT RECOVERY.

04:08.331 --> 04:09.708
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

04:09.750 --> 04:11.501
WHERE'S HARDISON AND PARKER?

04:11.543 --> 04:14.171
I SENT THEM ON AHEAD. YOU'LL

04:11.543 --> 04:14.171
UNDERSTAND AFTER THE BRIEFING.

04:14.213 --> 04:16.173
SOPHIE.

04:16.215 --> 04:20.427
THE "PAINTER

04:16.215 --> 04:20.427
ON THE ROAD TO TARASCON."

04:20.468 --> 04:21.929
IT'S A SELF-PORTRAIT

04:20.468 --> 04:21.929
BY VINCENT VAN GOGH

04:21.970 --> 04:24.431
COMPLETED IN 1888.

04:24.472 --> 04:27.267
IT WAS CONFISCATED BY THE NAZIS

04:24.472 --> 04:27.267
AS PART OF HITLER'S DRIVE

04:27.308 --> 04:29.644
TO ACCUMULATE ALL THE GREAT

04:27.308 --> 04:29.644
EUROPEAN WORKS OF ART.

04:29.686 --> 04:32.313
IT WAS HANGING IN A MUSEUM

04:29.686 --> 04:32.313
IN GERMANY

04:32.355 --> 04:33.774
WHEN ALLIED BOMBING

04:32.355 --> 04:33.774
SET THE PLACE ON FIRE

04:33.815 --> 04:35.358
AND IT WAS DESTROYED.

04:35.400 --> 04:37.194
THERE'S ALWAYS BEEN RUMORS

04:35.400 --> 04:37.194
THAT IT SURVIVED,

04:37.236 --> 04:39.863
BUT IT'S NEVER RESURFACED.

04:39.905 --> 04:41.698
-UNTIL NOW.

04:39.905 --> 04:41.698
-WE THINK.

04:41.740 --> 04:43.700
AN OLD COLLEAGUE OF MINE

04:41.740 --> 04:43.700
BELIEVES IT WAS SMUGGLED

04:43.742 --> 04:46.161
BACK INTO THE U.S. BY AN

04:43.742 --> 04:46.161
AMERICAN G.I. AFTER THE WAR.

04:46.203 --> 04:47.662
WHAT'S IT WORTH?

04:47.704 --> 04:50.040
JUDGING BY RECENT AUCTIONS,

04:47.704 --> 04:50.040
I'D SAY...

04:50.082 --> 04:53.376
$100 MILLION, GIVE OR TAKE.

04:53.418 --> 04:55.378
WHICH, UH, BRINGS US

04:53.418 --> 04:55.378
TO YOUR FORMER LINE

04:53.418 --> 04:55.378
OF WORK -- RETRIEVAL.

04:55.420 --> 04:57.839
HOW MUCH TROUBLE DO YOU THINK

04:55.420 --> 04:57.839
THIS ELDERLY VETERAN IS IN?

04:57.881 --> 05:00.717
FINDER'S FEE ON AN ITEM

04:57.881 --> 05:00.717
LIKE THIS IS PROBABLY 10%,

05:00.759 --> 05:05.764
SO IT DEPENDS WHAT YOU THINK

05:00.759 --> 05:05.764
A MAN WILL DO FOR $10 MILLION.

05:08.349 --> 05:10.727
NATE, WE'RE IN.

05:08.349 --> 05:10.727
TARGET IS SECURE.

05:12.312 --> 05:14.022
WELL, IF NOTHING HERE

05:12.312 --> 05:14.022
CATCHES YOUR FANCY,

05:14.064 --> 05:15.356
I CAN ALWAYS COME BACK LATER.

05:15.398 --> 05:17.525
UH, I-I'M FINE, THANK YOU.

05:17.567 --> 05:19.153
I-IN FACT,

05:17.567 --> 05:19.153
I'VE GOT TO GET OUT OF HERE.

05:19.194 --> 05:20.695
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

05:19.194 --> 05:20.695
RELAX, MR. LAWSON.

05:20.737 --> 05:22.405
IT'S OKAY.

05:20.737 --> 05:22.405
WE'RE HERE TO KEEP YOU SAFE.

05:22.447 --> 05:24.241
OKAY?

05:24.283 --> 05:26.160
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

05:26.201 --> 05:27.661
WE'RE NOT GONNA LET ANYTHING

05:26.201 --> 05:27.661
HAPPEN TO YOU. I PROMISE.

05:27.702 --> 05:29.621
JUST RELAX.

05:31.123 --> 05:33.416
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

05:34.835 --> 05:37.296
OKAY, IF YOU NEED ANYTHING ELSE,

05:34.835 --> 05:37.296
ANYTHING AT ALL,

05:37.336 --> 05:39.631
JUST CALL ME, OKAY?

05:39.673 --> 05:41.758
OKAY, DID YOU GET WHAT

05:39.673 --> 05:41.758
YOU NEEDED FROM HIS WALLET?

05:41.800 --> 05:43.718
GIRL, I HAD TO GO DOWN

05:41.800 --> 05:43.718
TO THE HALL OF RECORDS.

05:43.760 --> 05:45.553
YOU KNOW WHAT THE DUST

05:43.760 --> 05:45.553
DOES TO MY SINUSES.

05:45.595 --> 05:47.388
I CAN'T HALF BREATHE.

05:45.595 --> 05:47.388
I'M ABOUT TO SUFFOCATE.

05:47.430 --> 05:48.723
I KNOW.

05:48.765 --> 05:50.142
IT'S OKAY.

05:48.765 --> 05:50.142
WHAT DID YOU FIND?

05:50.184 --> 05:52.435
NOT MUCH. BIRTH CERTIFICATE.

05:50.184 --> 05:52.435
BUNCH OF OLD ADDRESSES.

05:52.477 --> 05:55.605
HE LEFT THE COUNTRY IN 1945

05:52.477 --> 05:55.605
AND NEVER CAME --

05:55.647 --> 05:57.107
CAME -- CAME BACK.

05:57.149 --> 05:59.109
[ SNEEZES ]

05:59.151 --> 06:00.986
-THANK YOU.

05:59.151 --> 06:00.986
-YOU'RE WELCOME.

06:01.028 --> 06:02.154
COME ON.

06:02.196 --> 06:04.198
[ CART ROLLING ]

06:04.239 --> 06:05.448
[ BEEP ]

06:05.490 --> 06:07.617
WHERE YOU AT?

06:07.659 --> 06:09.619
I'M IN A DAMN STORAGE CLOSET!

06:09.661 --> 06:12.580
SMELLS LIKE MOTHBALLS

06:09.661 --> 06:12.580
AND OLD PEOPLE.

06:12.622 --> 06:15.125
HARDISON, WHAT CAN YOU TELL US

06:12.622 --> 06:15.125
ABOUT CHARLIE LAWSON?

06:15.167 --> 06:16.584
WELL, HE'S 88 YEARS YOUNG.

06:16.626 --> 06:18.461
HE LIVED AND WORKED

06:16.626 --> 06:18.461
ALL OVER THE WORLD --

06:18.503 --> 06:20.379
FRANCE, BOTSWANA, AUSTRALIA.

06:20.421 --> 06:22.549
HIS PASSPORT SHOWS THAT

06:20.421 --> 06:22.549
HE CAME BACK TO WILLAMETTE CITY

06:22.590 --> 06:24.051
FOR THE FIRST TIME

06:22.590 --> 06:24.051
SINCE THE WAR.

06:24.092 --> 06:26.803
IT'S HIS HOMETOWN.

06:26.845 --> 06:28.222
THE SAME WEEK, HE'S IDENTIFIED

06:28.263 --> 06:29.764
AS A SUSPECT IN THE

06:28.263 --> 06:29.764
DISAPPEARANCE OF THE PAINTING.

06:29.806 --> 06:31.599
COINCIDENCE?

06:31.641 --> 06:33.935
OH, I THINK THAT PAINTING IS

06:31.641 --> 06:33.935
HIDDEN SOMEWHERE IN THAT TOWN.

06:33.977 --> 06:35.312
WE NEED TO FIND IT.

06:35.354 --> 06:39.149
YEAH, OR THAT OLD MAN

06:35.354 --> 06:39.149
IS GONNA BE HURT OR...WORSE.

06:39.191 --> 06:41.442
OR -- BUT -- NOT --

06:39.191 --> 06:41.442
NO, NOT -- NOT A TOY.

06:41.484 --> 06:42.861
WHAT, MAN?

06:42.903 --> 06:45.155
HE'S TELLING ME TO LEARN

06:42.903 --> 06:45.155
TECHNICAL STUFF ALL THE TIME.

06:45.197 --> 06:46.656
WELL, THAT'LL NEVER HAPPEN.

06:46.698 --> 06:48.116
WE GOT A PLANE TO CATCH.

06:55.207 --> 06:56.499
[ BELL TOLLING ]

06:56.541 --> 06:58.835
I DON'T HAVE ANY PAINTING.

06:58.877 --> 07:01.796
MR. LAWSON, UH,

06:58.877 --> 07:01.796
WE ARE NOT THE POLICE.

07:01.838 --> 07:04.966
I DON'T CARE IF YOU'RE

07:01.838 --> 07:04.966
VINCENT VAN GOGH HIMSELF.

07:05.008 --> 07:06.467
I CAN'T HELP YOU.

07:06.509 --> 07:09.679
MR. LAWSON, THIS PAINTING

07:06.509 --> 07:09.679
IS A LOST MASTERPIECE.

07:09.721 --> 07:10.764
IT BELONGS IN A MUSEUM.

07:10.805 --> 07:12.473
THE LONGER YOU STAY QUIET

07:10.805 --> 07:12.473
ABOUT IT,

07:12.515 --> 07:14.309
THE MORE DANGER

07:12.515 --> 07:14.309
YOU'RE GONNA BE IN.

07:14.351 --> 07:15.977
I'VE BEEN ON MY OWN A LONG TIME.

07:16.019 --> 07:17.771
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

07:17.812 --> 07:20.190
ALL RIGHT, WELL,

07:17.812 --> 07:20.190
IF YOU CHANGE YOUR MIND,

07:20.232 --> 07:23.068
GIVE ME A CALL.

07:25.904 --> 07:28.698
WHAT?

07:25.904 --> 07:28.698
NO, WAIT. WAIT.

07:28.740 --> 07:29.991
WE CAN'T JUST LEAVE.

07:31.785 --> 07:34.371
I'LL TALK TO NATE.

07:31.785 --> 07:34.371
WE'LL THINK OF SOMETHING.

07:34.413 --> 07:36.539
OKAY.

07:36.581 --> 07:37.707
WAIT.

07:39.251 --> 07:41.878
I'LL TELL YOU

07:39.251 --> 07:41.878
WHAT YOU WANT TO KNOW.

07:41.920 --> 07:43.546
BUT I'LL ONLY TALK WITH HER.

07:45.048 --> 07:47.634
THIS IS REALLY A JOB FOR SOPHIE.

07:47.675 --> 07:49.928
-HE DIDN'T ASK FOR SOPHIE.

07:47.675 --> 07:49.928
-YEAH, BUT, I MEAN,

07:47.675 --> 07:49.928
WHAT DO I DO?

07:49.970 --> 07:51.638
PLAY THE STATUS GAME,

07:49.970 --> 07:51.638
MIMIC HIS EMOTIONS,

07:51.679 --> 07:53.432
DISRUPT HIS TIMELINE

07:51.679 --> 07:53.432
TO KEEP HIM FROM LYING?

07:53.473 --> 07:55.100
ALL RIGHT, YOU  LISTEN.

07:55.142 --> 07:56.517
I HAVE NO IDEA

07:55.142 --> 07:56.517
WHAT HE'S GONNA SAY TO YOU,

07:56.559 --> 07:57.852
BUT RIGHT NOW

07:56.559 --> 07:57.852
HE'S THE ONLY LEAD WE HAVE.

07:57.894 --> 07:59.687
WE'LL FOLLOW HIS CLUES.

07:59.729 --> 08:02.983
JUST LISTEN.

08:03.024 --> 08:04.234
ALL RIGHT, NATE,

08:04.276 --> 08:06.027
I'M AT CHARLIE LAWSON'S HOUSE

08:04.276 --> 08:06.027
HE GREW UP IN.

08:06.069 --> 08:07.528
YOU SURE THIS IS WORTH IT?

08:07.570 --> 08:09.406
We got to start somewhere.

08:09.448 --> 08:10.907
HI.

08:10.949 --> 08:12.909
HOW YOU DOING, MA'AM?

08:10.949 --> 08:12.909
I'M WITH THE GAS COMPANY.

08:12.951 --> 08:15.412
WE'VE HAD A COUPLE OF REPORTS OF

08:12.951 --> 08:15.412
GAS LEAKS IN THE NEIGHBORHOOD,

08:15.454 --> 08:16.955
AND SO, UH,

08:15.454 --> 08:16.955
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND,

08:16.997 --> 08:18.957
JUST -- MIGHT HAVE TO

08:16.997 --> 08:18.957
GET UP IN THERE.

08:16.997 --> 08:18.957
[ BEEPING ]

08:18.999 --> 08:21.126
UH, AND THERE WE ARE.

08:21.168 --> 08:22.627
OH, BOY.

08:21.168 --> 08:22.627
THAT'S A -- THAT'S A --

08:22.669 --> 08:24.171
THAT'S A LEVEL ONE RIGHT THERE.

08:24.212 --> 08:25.839
YOU'VE GOT 84% L.O.L.

08:25.880 --> 08:27.215
SO, IF YOU COULD DO ME A FAVOR

08:27.257 --> 08:29.259
AND JUST STEP OUT ON THE PORCH

08:27.257 --> 08:29.259
JUST FOR A SECOND?

08:29.301 --> 08:30.718
I'M GONNA CHECK THE REST

08:29.301 --> 08:30.718
OF THE HOUSE.

08:30.760 --> 08:32.304
-SHOULDN'T TAKE

08:30.760 --> 08:32.304
BUT JUST A MINUTE. OKAY.

08:30.760 --> 08:32.304
-ALL RIGHT.

08:32.346 --> 08:35.307
WAIT. YOU'LL HAVE TO TELL THE

08:32.346 --> 08:35.307
MOLD INSPECTOR. HE'S OUT BACK.

08:36.933 --> 08:38.935
IS HE?

08:46.651 --> 08:47.861
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE, FRANK?

08:47.902 --> 08:50.613
RETIRING.

09:06.296 --> 09:09.632
BARBIE LEAVE THAT

09:06.296 --> 09:09.632
IN HER DREAM HOUSE?

09:09.674 --> 09:12.177
FRANK.

09:17.932 --> 09:19.726
[ DOOR OPENS ]

09:19.767 --> 09:22.145
SIR, IS EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

09:25.232 --> 09:26.483
[ DOG BARKING ]

09:26.525 --> 09:29.236
YEAH, YOUR, UH -- YOUR

09:26.525 --> 09:29.236
MOLD INSPECTOR JUST LEFT.

09:29.277 --> 09:30.404
HE SAID YOU'RE ALL CLEAR.

09:30.445 --> 09:31.738
WHAT ABOUT THE GAS LEAK?

09:31.779 --> 09:34.408
I'M STILL LOOKING FOR A SOURCE,

09:31.779 --> 09:34.408
UH, FOR THAT.

09:34.449 --> 09:36.451
I-I NEED TO KNOW WHAT YEAR

09:34.449 --> 09:36.451
THE HOUSE WAS BUILT.

09:36.493 --> 09:38.119
YOU DON'T HAVE

09:36.493 --> 09:38.119
ANY ORIGINAL FEATURES

09:38.161 --> 09:40.621
THAT WOULD HELP ME PINPOINT

09:38.161 --> 09:40.621
THE YEAR, DO YOU?

09:40.663 --> 09:41.956
NO.

09:41.998 --> 09:44.334
BUT I DID FIND SOME OLD ART.

09:47.628 --> 09:49.923
THAT MIGHT HELP.

09:49.964 --> 09:53.260
IT ALL STARTED

09:49.964 --> 09:53.260
AT THE ROLLER PALACE.

09:53.301 --> 09:54.719
WHEN I WAS A KID,

09:54.761 --> 09:58.390
IT SEEMS EVERYONE IN TOWN

09:54.761 --> 09:58.390
WAS THERE ON A SATURDAY NIGHT.

09:58.432 --> 10:01.893
THAT'S WHERE I MET HER.

10:01.935 --> 10:03.061
HERE YOU GO.

10:03.103 --> 10:05.230
[ COIN RATTLES ]

10:05.272 --> 10:07.232
HER NAME WAS DOROTHY ROSS.

10:07.274 --> 10:08.900
[ ORGAN PLAYING ]

10:08.942 --> 10:11.236
SHE WAS THE DAUGHTER

10:08.942 --> 10:11.236
OF ALFRED ROSS,

10:11.278 --> 10:15.073
A LUMBER BARON

10:11.278 --> 10:15.073
WHO OWNED HALF THE TOWN.

10:16.699 --> 10:18.826
SHE USED TO HAVE HER LESSONS

10:18.868 --> 10:22.997
ON THE WURLITZER AT THE PALACE.

10:23.039 --> 10:24.332
SOON WE BECAME FRIENDS.

10:24.374 --> 10:26.667
WHAT WAS SHE LIKE?

10:26.709 --> 10:28.503
SHE WAS STUBBORN AS A MULE.

10:28.545 --> 10:29.837
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

10:29.879 --> 10:32.173
SHE WOULDN'T LISTEN TO ANYBODY.

10:32.215 --> 10:34.175
HER DADDY WANTED HER

10:32.215 --> 10:34.175
TO BE A SOCIETY GIRL,

10:34.217 --> 10:37.971
BUT SHE WAS GONNA

10:34.217 --> 10:37.971
BE HER OWN PERSON.

10:38.012 --> 10:39.639
W-WHEN WE FIRST MET,

10:39.680 --> 10:43.643
I THOUGHT DOROTHY ROSS HAD --

10:39.680 --> 10:43.643
HAD IT ALL.

10:43.684 --> 10:45.312
BIG HOUSE, FANCY CLOTHES.

10:45.353 --> 10:49.483
BUT AS I GOT OLDER,

10:45.353 --> 10:49.483
I REALIZED...

10:49.524 --> 10:52.235
SHE WAS JUST AS TRAPPED

10:49.524 --> 10:52.235
AS I WAS.

10:53.903 --> 10:56.697
[ ORGAN PLAYING ]

10:53.903 --> 10:56.697
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING?

10:56.739 --> 10:59.033
THE EMPIRE STATE BUILDING!

10:59.075 --> 11:01.035
THAT'S IT?

10:59.075 --> 11:01.035
THAT'S WHERE YOU WANT TO GO?

11:01.077 --> 11:05.206
DOROTHY, I SAID

11:01.077 --> 11:05.206
ANYPLACE IN THE WORLD!

11:05.248 --> 11:07.375
NEW YORK CITY  IS  IN THE WORLD.

11:07.417 --> 11:09.377
I'VE NEVER BEEN THERE.

11:07.417 --> 11:09.377
HAVE YOU?

11:09.419 --> 11:12.172
NEW YORK CITY IS A PLACE

11:09.419 --> 11:12.172
WHERE YOU GET ON A BOAT.

11:12.213 --> 11:16.217
HOW ABOUT...THE TAJ MAHAL?

11:16.259 --> 11:19.554
WELL, SURE -- YOU DIDN'T SAY

11:16.259 --> 11:19.554
WHAT  PALACES  I WANTED TO VISIT.

11:19.596 --> 11:22.890
THE TAJ MAHAL ISN'T A PALACE.

11:19.596 --> 11:22.890
NO ONE LIVED THERE.

11:22.932 --> 11:25.810
IT'S A MAUSOLEUM THE SHAH

11:22.932 --> 11:25.810
BUILT FOR HIS DEAD WIFE.

11:25.852 --> 11:27.937
HOW DO YOU KNOW SO MUCH

11:25.852 --> 11:27.937
ABOUT THE WORLD?

11:27.979 --> 11:30.565
OH, THEY STILL LET ME

11:27.979 --> 11:30.565
IN THE LIBRARY.

11:30.607 --> 11:32.733
I DID NOT MEAN IT LIKE THAT.

11:32.775 --> 11:34.986
I GUESS I DON'T HAVE

11:32.775 --> 11:34.986
YOUR IMAGINATION.

11:36.571 --> 11:40.241
I DON'T IMAGINE.

11:36.571 --> 11:40.241
I PLAN.

11:48.500 --> 11:50.293
NATE, THIS TOWN'S CRAWLING

11:48.500 --> 11:50.293
WITH TREASURE HUNTERS.

11:50.335 --> 11:52.128
I'LL DO A SWEEP

11:50.335 --> 11:52.128
AND REPORT BACK TO YOU.

11:52.170 --> 11:55.632
BUT DO NOT LET CHARLIE

11:52.170 --> 11:55.632
LEAVE THE HOSPITAL.

11:55.674 --> 11:58.968
-I FOUND THIS BEHIND A WALL

11:55.674 --> 11:58.968
WHEN WE FIRST MOVED IN.

11:55.674 --> 11:58.968
-Stand by.

11:59.010 --> 12:01.179
COULDN'T BEAR TO THROW IT AWAY.

12:05.600 --> 12:09.229
DOES THIS HELP YOU?

12:09.270 --> 12:12.232
NO, BUT IT LOOKS LIKE

12:09.270 --> 12:12.232
SOMEBODY THAT LIVED HERE

12:12.273 --> 12:13.567
REALLY WANTED TO VISIT --

12:13.608 --> 12:15.235
-THE EIFFEL TOWER!

12:13.608 --> 12:15.235
-YEAH.

12:15.276 --> 12:16.611
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

12:16.653 --> 12:19.614
THAT'S WHERE DOROTHY

12:16.653 --> 12:19.614
WANTED TO GO, TOO!

12:19.656 --> 12:20.990
HER DADDY WAS THRILLED

12:21.032 --> 12:23.993
SHE WAS FINALLY ASPIRING

12:21.032 --> 12:23.993
TO THE FINER THINGS IN LIFE.

12:24.035 --> 12:25.245
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:25.286 --> 12:27.955
OH, SO HE STARTED GIVING HER

12:25.286 --> 12:27.955
FRENCH LESSONS.

12:27.997 --> 12:30.625
WHAT HE DIDN'T KNOW --

12:27.997 --> 12:30.625
THAT SHE WAS TURNING AROUND

12:30.667 --> 12:32.793
AND TEACHING ME FRENCH, TOO.

12:32.835 --> 12:34.170
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

12:34.212 --> 12:37.507
"PLEASE TELL ME WHERE I CAN FIND

12:34.212 --> 12:37.507
THE NEAREST BAKERY."

12:37.549 --> 12:40.427
S'IL VOUS PLAîT, OU SE TROUVE

12:37.549 --> 12:40.427
LA BOULANGERIE LA PLUS PROCHE?

12:40.468 --> 12:43.096
HMM.

12:43.137 --> 12:45.181
"THE LAST BOAT LEFT AN HOUR AGO.

12:45.223 --> 12:47.308
YOU'LL HAVE TO TAKE THE BRIDGE."

12:47.350 --> 12:48.976
LE DERNIER BâTEAU EST PARTI

12:47.350 --> 12:48.976
DEPUIS UNE HEURE.

12:49.018 --> 12:50.228
IL VOUS FAUT PASSER

12:49.018 --> 12:50.228
PAR LE PONT.

12:50.270 --> 12:51.854
OH, FOR PETE'S SAKE!

12:51.896 --> 12:54.524
I HAVE A PRIVATE TUTOR, BUT YOU

12:51.896 --> 12:54.524
SPEAK BETTER FRENCH THAN I DO!

12:54.566 --> 12:57.902
POUR L'AMOUR DU CIEL,

12:54.566 --> 12:57.902
J'AI UN PROFESSEUR PARTICULIER,

12:57.944 --> 13:00.821
MAIS TOI TU PARLES LE FRANçAIS

12:57.944 --> 13:00.821
MIEUX QUE MOI.

13:00.863 --> 13:03.157
I JUST HAVE AN EAR

13:00.863 --> 13:03.157
FOR LANGUAGES.

13:03.199 --> 13:05.285
I'D SAY YOU'RE READY TO GO

13:03.199 --> 13:05.285
TO FRANCE RIGHT NOW.

13:05.326 --> 13:07.621
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

13:07.662 --> 13:10.998
MAYBE WE CAN GO TOGETHER,

13:07.662 --> 13:10.998
AFTER THE GERMANS LEAVE.

13:11.040 --> 13:14.586
I SAID IT AS A JOKE,

13:14.628 --> 13:17.922
JUST SO I COULD TAKE IT BACK,

13:14.628 --> 13:17.922
BUT I MEANT EVERY WORD OF IT.

13:17.964 --> 13:21.926
I WAS IN LOVE WITH DOROTHY ROSS.

13:21.968 --> 13:24.887
I'D LIKE THAT.

13:24.929 --> 13:26.681
[ DOOR OPENS ]

13:24.929 --> 13:26.681
DOROTHY!

13:26.723 --> 13:27.682
DADDY!

13:27.724 --> 13:29.392
OH, I DROPPED MY BOOK.

13:29.434 --> 13:32.270
CHARLIE WAS JUST HELPING ME.

13:32.312 --> 13:34.021
OF COURSE.

13:32.312 --> 13:34.021
HOW'S YOUR MAMA?

13:34.063 --> 13:35.690
SHE STILL WORKING

13:34.063 --> 13:35.690
FOR HAROLD DOLE'S FAMILY?

13:35.732 --> 13:37.692
YES, SIR.

13:35.732 --> 13:37.692
GOING ON 20 YEARS NOW.

13:37.734 --> 13:39.026
GOOD.

13:39.068 --> 13:40.819
WELL, YOU GIVE YOUR MOTHER

13:39.068 --> 13:40.819
MY REGARDS, WON'T YOU?

13:40.861 --> 13:43.406
YES, I'LL DO THAT, MR. ROSS.

13:45.450 --> 13:47.410
YOU LOOK SPLENDID TODAY.

13:47.452 --> 13:49.245
THANK YOU.

13:49.287 --> 13:51.748
NOW, WILLAMETTE CITY

13:49.287 --> 13:51.748
IS NOT SELMA, ALABAMA,

13:51.790 --> 13:53.291
BUT IT WAS 1942.

13:53.333 --> 13:56.628
AND A BLACK MAN MAKING OVERTURES

13:53.333 --> 13:56.628
TO A WHITE WOMAN

13:56.670 --> 13:58.963
WAS LITERALLY A CRIME.

13:59.005 --> 14:02.049
BUT I HAD GOTTEN AWAY WITH IT.

14:03.968 --> 14:06.805
OR SO I THOUGHT.

14:03.968 --> 14:06.805
[ GRUNTS ]

14:06.845 --> 14:08.598
HEY!

14:13.353 --> 14:15.730
WHAT DID I DO?

14:15.772 --> 14:18.608
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU DID.

14:19.776 --> 14:21.402
AND I'M JUST GETTING STARTED.

14:21.444 --> 14:24.572
WELL, WHAT YOU WAITING ON?

14:21.444 --> 14:24.572
HIT ME! HIT ME!

14:24.614 --> 14:26.783
[ GUN COCKS ]

14:29.035 --> 14:30.328
LEWIS.

14:30.370 --> 14:32.455
I WAS WONDERING WHAT

14:30.370 --> 14:32.455
YOUR CAR WAS DOING HERE.

14:32.497 --> 14:33.832
SHERIFF.

14:33.873 --> 14:35.916
THIS SPOOK TRIED TO HAVE

14:33.873 --> 14:35.916
HIS WAY WITH THE ROSS GIRL.

14:35.958 --> 14:38.586
-IT'S A LIE!

14:35.958 --> 14:38.586
-EASY, CHARLIE.

14:38.628 --> 14:41.255
NOW, LEWIS, YOU RUN

14:38.628 --> 14:41.255
MR. ROSS' MILL, RIGHT?

14:41.297 --> 14:42.549
YES, SIR.

14:42.590 --> 14:44.759
DOES THAT JOB COME

14:42.590 --> 14:44.759
WITH A BADGE NOW, TOO?

14:46.386 --> 14:48.012
YOU'RE MAKING A MISTAKE,

14:46.386 --> 14:48.012
SHERIFF.

14:48.054 --> 14:49.972
WELL, IT WON'T BE MY FIRST TIME.

14:50.014 --> 14:52.308
NOW GET ON.

14:55.854 --> 14:56.979
[ GRUNTS ]

14:57.021 --> 14:58.314
HELLO, CHARLIE.

14:58.356 --> 15:00.650
I'LL BE ALL RIGHT.

15:00.692 --> 15:01.818
NOW...

15:01.860 --> 15:04.153
MESSING WITH

15:01.860 --> 15:04.153
ALFRED ROSS' DAUGHTER --

15:04.195 --> 15:06.322
YOU ARE PLAYING WITH FIRE, SON.

15:06.364 --> 15:07.866
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

15:07.907 --> 15:09.200
WELL, NO, YOU CAN'T.

15:09.242 --> 15:11.202
NOW, I'M SHIPPING OFF

15:09.242 --> 15:11.202
TO TRAINING CAMP

15:11.244 --> 15:12.245
AND, AFTER THAT, THE WAR.

15:12.286 --> 15:13.538
THE DEPUTIES

15:12.286 --> 15:13.538
THAT I'M LEAVING BEHIND,

15:13.580 --> 15:15.081
THEY DON'T KNOW YOU

15:13.580 --> 15:15.081
AS WELL AS I DO,

15:15.122 --> 15:16.750
AND THEY'RE NOT GONNA

15:15.122 --> 15:16.750
GIVE A RAT'S TAIL

15:16.791 --> 15:18.251
IF THOSE BOYS COME BACK.

15:18.292 --> 15:20.420
I CAN PROMISE YOU THAT.

15:18.292 --> 15:20.420
ALL RIGHT?

15:20.461 --> 15:22.296
AND THEY WILL COME BACK.

15:24.298 --> 15:26.092
WHAT AM --

15:24.298 --> 15:26.092
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

15:26.133 --> 15:29.429
EVERYBODY'S GOT TO FIND

15:26.133 --> 15:29.429
THEIR OWN WAY RIGHT NOW.

15:29.470 --> 15:31.806
I'M JUST GIVING YOU

15:29.470 --> 15:31.806
THE LAY OF THE LAND.

15:36.227 --> 15:39.522
AT THAT MOMENT,

15:36.227 --> 15:39.522
I REALIZED I HAD TO DO SOMETHING

15:39.564 --> 15:44.193
TO CHANGE MR. ROSS' MIND

15:39.564 --> 15:44.193
ABOUT ME.

15:44.235 --> 15:46.195
MAYBE DOROTHY WAS RIGHT --

15:46.237 --> 15:49.282
MAYBE I  WAS  READY

15:46.237 --> 15:49.282
TO GO TO FRANCE.

15:49.323 --> 15:51.325
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

15:56.205 --> 15:57.874
-CHARLIE'S NOT HERE.

15:56.205 --> 15:57.874
-HUH?

15:59.542 --> 16:01.878
HE ENLISTED THIS MORNING.

16:15.934 --> 16:18.060
NOW, THERE WEREN'T

16:15.934 --> 16:18.060
A LOT OF CHOICES

16:18.102 --> 16:20.563
FOR A BLACK MAN IN THE ARMY.

16:20.605 --> 16:24.400
I DROVE A SUPPLY TRUCK

16:20.605 --> 16:24.400
AS PART OF THE RED BALL EXPRESS.

16:24.442 --> 16:26.736
[ CHUCKLES ]

16:24.442 --> 16:26.736
AND I WAS GOOD AT IT.

16:26.778 --> 16:28.738
AND I COULD USE MY FRENCH

16:28.780 --> 16:32.742
TO HORSE-TRADE

16:28.780 --> 16:32.742
FOR FOOD AND WINE AND WHATEVER.

16:32.784 --> 16:36.579
WELL, NOT THAT I GOT THE CHANCE

16:32.784 --> 16:36.579
TO ENJOY IT.

16:36.621 --> 16:40.750
IT WAS AFTER D-DAY, AND WE WERE

16:36.621 --> 16:40.750
CLEARING POCKETS OF GERMANS

16:40.792 --> 16:42.418
IN THE FRENCH COUNTRYSIDE.

16:42.460 --> 16:43.586
LET'S HOLD UP HERE.

16:43.628 --> 16:45.421
PARIS WAS GONNA HAVE TO WAIT.

16:45.463 --> 16:49.133
I NEED ANOTHER PINEAPPLE.

16:45.463 --> 16:49.133
THIS IS FROM THAT BATCH OF DUDS.

16:53.346 --> 16:55.723
NEED SOME AMMO, TOO.

16:58.518 --> 17:00.687
éCOUTEZ! AIDEZ-MOI, MONSIEUR,

16:58.518 --> 17:00.687
S'IL VOUS PLAîT!

17:00.728 --> 17:03.189
-FAITES DEMI-TOUR!

17:00.728 --> 17:03.189
C'EST DANGEREUX!

17:00.728 --> 17:03.189
-WHOA, WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

17:03.230 --> 17:04.941
-WHAT IS IT?

17:03.230 --> 17:04.941
-C'EST DANGEREUX, MONSIEUR!

17:04.983 --> 17:06.400
-GREAT. THE DAY

17:04.983 --> 17:06.400
I LOSE MY TRANSLATOR.

17:04.983 --> 17:06.400
-UN SOLDAT ALLEMAND.

17:06.442 --> 17:07.986
JE L'AI VU EN TRAIN

17:06.442 --> 17:07.986
DE VOLER DE MA FERME.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.821
-VOUS êTES EN DANGER.

17:08.027 --> 17:09.821
-WHAT THE HELL IS SHE SAYING?!

17:09.863 --> 17:11.739
HEY, SUPPLY.

17:09.863 --> 17:11.739
YOU LISTENING TO ME?

17:11.781 --> 17:14.868
KRAUTS! SHE'S SAYING KRAUTS!

17:11.781 --> 17:14.868
GET DOWN!

17:14.909 --> 17:16.035
[ GUNSHOT ]

17:14.909 --> 17:16.035
AAH!

17:16.076 --> 17:18.830
[ GUNFIRE ]

17:16.076 --> 17:18.830
AAH!  ALLEZ!

17:26.963 --> 17:29.423
[ GUNFIRE ]

17:26.963 --> 17:29.423
MY LEG!

17:31.885 --> 17:33.720
HE'S IN THE WOODS!

17:33.761 --> 17:35.429
LAY DOWN SUPPRESSION FIRE!

17:36.890 --> 17:39.141
-CAN YOU MOVE? MOVE TO ME!

17:36.890 --> 17:39.141
-[ GROANING ]

17:39.183 --> 17:40.393
[ GUNFIRE ]

17:40.434 --> 17:42.478
MOVE!

17:44.772 --> 17:47.901
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

17:47.942 --> 17:49.527
HELP ME! HELP ME!

17:49.569 --> 17:51.445
I NEED A POSITION!

17:51.487 --> 17:52.572
[ GUNFIRE ]

17:52.613 --> 17:54.240
GRENADE!

17:54.281 --> 17:57.326
MOVE IT!

17:57.368 --> 17:59.537
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

18:01.539 --> 18:03.708
COVER ME!

18:06.252 --> 18:08.504
[ GUNSHOT ]

18:11.591 --> 18:14.176
SUPPLY. SUPPLY!

18:14.218 --> 18:15.302
CHARLIE!

18:15.344 --> 18:17.513
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

18:25.312 --> 18:30.276
AH, IT DIDN'T MAKE SENSE THAT

18:25.312 --> 18:30.276
HE WOULD BE ALONE LIKE THIS.

18:30.317 --> 18:34.030
IN THE CHAOS OF THE INVASION,

18:30.317 --> 18:34.030
ANYTHING WAS POSSIBLE.

18:40.870 --> 18:42.329
TAKE THIS.

18:40.870 --> 18:42.329
TAKE HIS SUPPLIES.

18:42.371 --> 18:43.831
GIVE ME THE BAG.

18:43.873 --> 18:45.583
THERE MIGHT BE SOME INTEL

18:43.873 --> 18:45.583
ON THE MAPS.

18:45.625 --> 18:46.876
GO.

18:46.918 --> 18:48.502
[ GUN COCKS ]

18:50.964 --> 18:53.215
NICE SHOT, LAWSON.

18:53.257 --> 18:56.552
DID YOU HEAR HIM

18:53.257 --> 18:56.552
MENTION THE LETTERS, HUH?

18:56.594 --> 18:58.721
MAYBE IT  IS  TRUE.

18:58.763 --> 19:00.389
[ SNEEZES, GROANS ]

19:00.431 --> 19:01.724
-WHAT DO YOU GOT?

19:00.431 --> 19:01.724
-[ SNIFFS ]

19:01.766 --> 19:03.517
OH, PROBABLY JUST MY SENSITIVITY

19:01.766 --> 19:03.517
TO DUST MITES.

19:03.559 --> 19:04.978
IT'S WHAT HAPPENS

19:03.559 --> 19:04.978
WHEN YOU SEND ME

19:05.019 --> 19:06.938
-TO THE HALL OF RECORDS

19:05.019 --> 19:06.938
A SECOND --

19:05.019 --> 19:06.938
-NO, NO, NO. NO.

19:06.980 --> 19:09.189
DOROTHY ROSS. WHAT DO YOU

19:06.980 --> 19:09.189
HAVE ON DOROTHY ROSS?

19:09.231 --> 19:12.401
D-- SHE DIED.

19:12.443 --> 19:15.404
DOROTHY VAN BUREN,

19:12.443 --> 19:15.404
FORMERLY DOROTHY ROSS --

19:15.446 --> 19:17.406
SHE DIED THREE YEARS AGO.

19:17.448 --> 19:20.076
BUT IT LOOKS LIKE SHE SPENT

19:17.448 --> 19:20.076
HER WHOLE LIFE HERE IN TOWN,

19:20.118 --> 19:21.911
PLAYING THE WURLITZER

19:20.118 --> 19:21.911
OVER AT THE ROLLER PALACE.

19:21.953 --> 19:24.914
-SHE, UH -- SHE LEFT HER HOUSE

19:21.953 --> 19:24.914
TO HER DAUGHTER.

19:21.953 --> 19:24.914
-OH.

19:24.956 --> 19:26.248
THAT'S THE ADDRESS RIGHT THERE.

19:26.290 --> 19:27.834
-THERE'S A DAUGHTER.

19:26.290 --> 19:27.834
-YEAH.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.669
DOROTHY MARRIED SOME LOCAL GUY

19:27.875 --> 19:29.669
IN '57.

19:29.710 --> 19:30.920
HE DIED IN THE '90s.

19:30.962 --> 19:33.255
-I'LL CHECK IT OUT.

19:30.962 --> 19:33.255
-HMM.

19:33.297 --> 19:35.925
LIKE HANGING HERE IN A HOSPITAL

19:33.297 --> 19:35.925
IS ANY BETTER.

19:35.967 --> 19:37.677
YOU KNOW WHAT, MAN --

19:35.967 --> 19:37.677
IF I GET OUT OF THIS JOB

19:37.718 --> 19:39.971
-WITHOUT UPPER-RESPIRATORY

19:37.718 --> 19:39.971
ISSUES, IT WILL BE A MIRACLE.

19:37.718 --> 19:39.971
-YEAH.

19:40.013 --> 19:42.640
WHAT? REALLY? THIS?

19:40.013 --> 19:42.640
WHAT -- NASTY.

19:42.682 --> 19:44.475
DON'T KNOW WHERE THIS HAS BEEN.

19:44.517 --> 19:45.810
CONGRATULATIONS, PRIVATE.

19:45.852 --> 19:47.311
HE WAS STANDING OVER THERE, TOO,

19:47.353 --> 19:50.272
SO I DIDN'T HAVE ANY CHOICE,

19:47.353 --> 19:50.272
YOU KNOW.

19:50.314 --> 19:52.441
HEY.

19:50.314 --> 19:52.441
WHAT'S GOING ON?

19:52.483 --> 19:53.985
OH, McCLUSKY GOT HIS FIRST KILL.

19:54.027 --> 19:55.153
SAVED THE WHOLE UNIT.

19:55.194 --> 19:57.237
LIEUTENANT'S PUTTING HIM IN

19:55.194 --> 19:57.237
FOR A MEDAL.

19:57.279 --> 20:02.743
McCLUSKY --

19:57.279 --> 20:02.743
THE MAN WHO HID BEHIND MY TRUCK.

20:02.785 --> 20:04.244
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

20:06.122 --> 20:08.248
DID I SEND FOR YOU, SUPPLY?

20:08.290 --> 20:09.458
I KILLED THAT SNIPER.

20:09.500 --> 20:12.461
YOU KNOW IT. I KNOW IT.

20:09.500 --> 20:12.461
EVERYONE KNOWS IT.

20:12.503 --> 20:15.464
McCLUSKY FIRED THE SHOT.

20:12.503 --> 20:15.464
IT'S IN MY REPORT.

20:15.506 --> 20:17.175
IT'S A LIE.

20:17.216 --> 20:19.385
YOU'RE CALLING ME A LIAR?

20:19.426 --> 20:21.345
YES, SIR, I AM.

20:21.387 --> 20:22.513
THIS WAR IS ALMOST OVER.

20:22.555 --> 20:24.140
THINK ABOUT WHAT YOU'RE DOING

20:22.555 --> 20:24.140
RIGHT NOW.

20:24.182 --> 20:25.474
DON'T YOU TELL ME TO THINK,

20:24.182 --> 20:25.474
LIEUTENANT.

20:25.516 --> 20:29.145
MY THINKING SAVED YOUR LIFE!

20:29.187 --> 20:31.480
BUT I WON'T GET THE CREDIT

20:29.187 --> 20:31.480
BECAUSE I'M A NEGRO,

20:31.522 --> 20:32.773
ISN'T THAT RIGHT?

20:32.815 --> 20:35.026
THAT'S RIGHT.

20:36.610 --> 20:39.072
IT'S NOT THE POLICY

20:36.610 --> 20:39.072
OF THE UNITED STATES GOVERNMENT

20:39.113 --> 20:41.407
TO HAND OUT MEDALS TO NEGROES.

20:41.448 --> 20:42.950
THEREFORE, PRIVATE McCLUSKY

20:42.992 --> 20:44.911
FIRED THE SHOT

20:42.992 --> 20:44.911
THAT KILLED THE SNIPER,

20:44.952 --> 20:49.207
MAKING HIM, AND NOT YOU,

20:44.952 --> 20:49.207
A CANDIDATE FOR THE BRONZE STAR.

20:49.248 --> 20:52.210
THAT'S JUST THE WAY IT IS,

20:49.248 --> 20:52.210
CHARLIE.

20:52.251 --> 20:55.755
YOU DON'T HAVE TO LIKE IT,

20:52.251 --> 20:55.755
BUT THAT'S THE WAY IT IS.

21:09.351 --> 21:12.688
[ GRUNTS ]

21:37.296 --> 21:40.258
WHEN YOU SPEAK ENGLISH

21:37.296 --> 21:40.258
AND FRENCH,

21:40.299 --> 21:42.093
GERMAN'S NOT THAT HARD.

21:42.135 --> 21:44.428
THE LETTER

21:42.135 --> 21:44.428
WAS TO HIS GIRL BACK HOME,

21:44.470 --> 21:47.431
A GIRL HE'D NEVER SEE AGAIN

21:44.470 --> 21:47.431
BECAUSE OF ME.

21:47.473 --> 21:51.102
I DIDN'T HAVE TIME TO DWELL

21:47.473 --> 21:51.102
ON THIS UNFORTUNATE SITUATION

21:51.144 --> 21:52.937
BECAUSE OF WHAT I READ NEXT.

21:52.979 --> 21:56.816
IT WAS ABOUT A PAINTING

21:52.979 --> 21:56.816
HE HAD SAVED FROM THE FIRE...

21:58.276 --> 22:00.569
...AND HOW

21:58.276 --> 22:00.569
IT WOULD PROVIDE FOR THEM

22:00.611 --> 22:03.072
FOR THE REST OF THEIR LIVES.

22:03.114 --> 22:04.907
TAKE THIS.

22:03.114 --> 22:04.907
TAKE HIS SUPPLIES.

22:04.949 --> 22:06.033
GIVE ME THE BAG.

22:09.745 --> 22:12.706
THE SNIPER'S GEAR

22:09.745 --> 22:12.706
WAS IN HIS TENT.

22:12.748 --> 22:15.251
LIEUTENANT

22:12.748 --> 22:15.251
HADN'T LOOKED AT IT YET.

22:17.128 --> 22:20.631
I WAS THE ONLY ONE

22:17.128 --> 22:20.631
WHO KNEW ABOUT THE PAINTING.

22:33.186 --> 22:35.146
AT THAT MOMENT, I REALIZED

22:35.188 --> 22:39.192
THAT I DIDN'T HAVE TO BE A HERO

22:35.188 --> 22:39.192
TO GET DOROTHY.

22:44.197 --> 22:47.158
I HAD THE PAINTING.

22:47.200 --> 22:48.826
AND I HAD A PLAN.

22:51.620 --> 22:53.080
HOW CAN THEY TEAR DOWN

22:51.620 --> 22:53.080
THE ROLLER PALACE?

22:53.122 --> 22:55.415
MM. IT'S A LONG STORY.

22:55.457 --> 22:58.252
THE DEVELOPER PAID OFF

22:55.457 --> 22:58.252
THE PLANNING COMMISSION.

22:58.294 --> 22:59.920
MY LAW FIRM ARE TRYING TO HELP.

22:59.962 --> 23:01.463
WELL, YOU CAME

22:59.962 --> 23:01.463
TO THE RIGHT PLACE.

23:01.505 --> 23:04.466
MY MOM PLAYED THE WURLITZER

23:01.505 --> 23:04.466
AT THE ROLLER PALACE

23:04.508 --> 23:07.053
-FOR 50 YEARS.

23:04.508 --> 23:07.053
-SO I WAS TOLD.

23:07.094 --> 23:10.097
AND ANYTIME SOMEONE

23:07.094 --> 23:10.097
WOULD TRY TO TEAR IT DOWN,

23:10.139 --> 23:12.308
SHE WOULD FIGHT THEM

23:10.139 --> 23:12.308
TOOTH AND NAIL.

23:12.350 --> 23:14.143
SHE'D SIT RIGHT THERE

23:12.350 --> 23:14.143
AT HER OLD DESK,

23:14.185 --> 23:16.687
AND SHE WOULD WRITE A LETTER

23:14.185 --> 23:16.687
TO ANYONE WHO WOULD LISTEN.

23:16.729 --> 23:19.273
HMM. THIS IS HER.

23:19.315 --> 23:21.567
AH. OH.

23:21.608 --> 23:23.903
-SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.

23:21.608 --> 23:23.903
-SHE WAS.

23:23.944 --> 23:25.403
SHE PASSED AWAY THREE YEARS AGO.

23:25.445 --> 23:26.906
-OH, I'M SORRY.

23:25.445 --> 23:26.906
-MM.

23:26.947 --> 23:28.574
IT'S YOUR ACCENT.

23:28.615 --> 23:31.244
YOU REMIND ME

23:28.615 --> 23:31.244
OF MY AUNT CECILIA.

23:31.285 --> 23:33.746
SHE WAS A WAR BRIDE,

23:31.285 --> 23:33.746
AND SHE TAUGHT MY MOM

23:33.787 --> 23:35.413
TO PLAY THE WURLITZER ORGAN

23:33.787 --> 23:35.413
AT THE PALACE

23:35.455 --> 23:37.583
-AFTER THE WAR.

23:35.455 --> 23:37.583
-WOW.

23:37.624 --> 23:38.667
[ ORGAN PLAYING ]

23:45.674 --> 23:46.633
[ SIGHS ]

23:46.675 --> 23:48.344
OOH!

23:50.096 --> 23:52.472
YOU KNOW, YOUR FATHER

23:50.096 --> 23:52.472
PAYS ME BY THE HOUR.

23:52.514 --> 23:55.976
OH, COME ON, CECILIA.

23:52.514 --> 23:55.976
I'M JUST TAKING A BREAK!

23:56.018 --> 23:59.063
MY TEACHER WOULD RAP ME

23:56.018 --> 23:59.063
ON THE KNUCKLES WITH A RULER.

23:59.105 --> 24:02.482
WELL, THAT'S WHY I'M SO LUCKY

23:59.105 --> 24:02.482
YOU'RE  MY TEACHER!

24:02.524 --> 24:04.526
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:13.160 --> 24:17.290
THE FIRST TIME I SAW DOROTHY

24:13.160 --> 24:17.290
SINCE I LEFT FOR THE WAR,

24:17.331 --> 24:20.667
IT WAS LIKE

24:17.331 --> 24:20.667
SHE WAS FLOATING ON AIR.

24:22.586 --> 24:24.088
[ DOOR OPENS ]

24:29.551 --> 24:31.595
DOROTHY!

24:33.764 --> 24:36.725
IT'S OKAY, CECILIA.

24:36.767 --> 24:39.228
HE'S AN OLD FRIEND.

24:40.313 --> 24:43.523
CHARLIE.

24:43.565 --> 24:45.109
WHEN DID YOU GET BACK?

24:45.151 --> 24:46.777
DOESN'T MATTER.

24:46.819 --> 24:48.612
I NEED TO SPEAK WITH YOU.

24:48.654 --> 24:50.406
ALONE.

24:50.448 --> 24:51.991
YEAH.

24:52.032 --> 24:53.993
I CAN SEE THE ROLLER PALACE

24:52.032 --> 24:53.993
MEANT THE WORLD TO YOUR MOTHER.

24:54.034 --> 24:55.202
IT DID.

24:55.244 --> 24:57.746
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

24:55.244 --> 24:57.746
OH, EXCUSE ME.

24:59.373 --> 25:01.167
[ BEEP ]

24:59.373 --> 25:01.167
HELLO?

25:01.208 --> 25:02.500
[ Indian accent ]

25:01.208 --> 25:02.500
HELLO, MISS PORTER?

25:02.542 --> 25:04.420
THIS IS CHAD JONES CALLING

25:02.542 --> 25:04.420
FROM CREDIT SERVICES.

25:04.462 --> 25:07.423
THERE HAS BEEN SOME UNUSUAL

25:04.462 --> 25:07.423
ACTIVITY ON YOUR CREDIT CARD.

25:07.465 --> 25:09.549
DID YOU, BY CHANCE,

25:07.465 --> 25:09.549
PURCHASE A JET SKI?

25:09.591 --> 25:10.801
I'M SORRY, A WHAT?

25:10.843 --> 25:12.594
I have some more charges

25:10.843 --> 25:12.594
I need you to confirm.

25:12.636 --> 25:14.388
OKAY, THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

25:12.636 --> 25:14.388
LET ME GET MY CARD.

25:14.430 --> 25:15.389
JUST A MINUTE.

25:15.431 --> 25:17.183
I'M SORRY.

25:15.431 --> 25:17.183
WILL YOU EXCUSE ME?

25:17.224 --> 25:19.435
-OH. NO PROBLEM. I'LL, UH --

25:17.224 --> 25:19.435
I'LL JUST LOOK AT THE BOOK.

25:17.224 --> 25:19.435
-OH. OKAY.

25:21.020 --> 25:22.313
I'M CLEAR.

25:22.355 --> 25:23.981
THERE'S NO SIGN

25:22.355 --> 25:23.981
OF THE PAINTING HERE,

25:24.023 --> 25:26.484
BUT I'VE GOT A LEAD.

25:35.159 --> 25:36.660
AHH.

25:38.787 --> 25:40.747
HMM.

25:40.789 --> 25:45.252
HELLO, LITTLE HIDDEN KEY

25:40.789 --> 25:45.252
TO A SAFETY-DEPOSIT BOX.

25:45.294 --> 25:48.255
MISS PORTER, I'M ALMOST DONE

25:45.294 --> 25:48.255
EXPUNGING THESE FALSE CHARGES

25:48.297 --> 25:49.423
FROM YOUR CREDIT CARD.

25:49.465 --> 25:51.091
IT WILL JUST BE ANOTHER MOMENT.

25:51.133 --> 25:53.719
[ Normal voice ] GUYS. GUYS,

25:51.133 --> 25:53.719
THAT PAINTING'S ONLY 18 INCHES.

25:53.760 --> 25:55.721
That can easily fit

25:53.760 --> 25:55.721
inside a safety-deposit box.

25:55.762 --> 25:59.517
OR SHE COULD HAVE SOLD IT

25:55.762 --> 25:59.517
AND STASHED THE CASH.

25:59.557 --> 26:01.685
SOPHIE, HARDISON, UH,

25:59.557 --> 26:01.685
OPEN THAT SAFE-DEPOSIT BOX.

26:01.727 --> 26:03.937
UH, ELIOT, I WANT YOU TO SECURE

26:01.727 --> 26:03.937
THE BANK'S PERIMETER.

26:03.979 --> 26:07.358
Parker, you're doing

26:03.979 --> 26:07.358
a great job. Keep it up.

26:07.400 --> 26:11.028
REMEMBER WHEN I ASKED YOU

26:07.400 --> 26:11.028
TO GO TO PARIS WITH ME?

26:11.070 --> 26:12.196
WELL, NOW WE CAN.

26:12.238 --> 26:14.198
W-WE CAN SELL THIS PAINTING

26:12.238 --> 26:14.198
IN NEW YORK,

26:14.240 --> 26:16.033
NEVER COME BACK

26:14.240 --> 26:16.033
TO THIS TOWN AGAIN.

26:16.075 --> 26:18.869
WE CAN GO TO ALL THE PLACES

26:16.075 --> 26:18.869
THAT YOU WANT TO GO, TOGETHER.

26:18.911 --> 26:22.164
NOBODY CAN STOP US.

26:22.206 --> 26:24.250
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

26:24.291 --> 26:27.794
I SAY YES.

26:29.629 --> 26:32.216
HOW DO WE DO IT?

26:32.258 --> 26:35.052
WELL, YOU'RE PLAYING THE

26:32.258 --> 26:35.052
WURLITZER TOMORROW NIGHT, RIGHT?

26:35.094 --> 26:36.720
EVERYONE IN TOWN WILL BE HERE.

26:36.762 --> 26:39.223
THAT'S WHEN WE'LL DO IT.

26:39.265 --> 26:40.349
BUT YOU'LL NEED HELP.

26:43.561 --> 26:45.271
SHE'LL DO IT.

26:45.312 --> 26:48.065
OKAY.

26:48.107 --> 26:51.735
HERE IT IS.

26:48.107 --> 26:51.735
STEP BY STEP.

26:51.777 --> 26:53.611
WE CAN DO THIS.

26:53.653 --> 26:56.198
SOMEONE'S COMING!

26:58.742 --> 27:01.579
MY FRENCH.

26:58.742 --> 27:01.579
IT'S STILL TERRIBLE.

27:01.619 --> 27:03.789
I KNOW.

27:20.389 --> 27:21.848
[ SMOOCHES ]

27:21.890 --> 27:23.683
HOW WAS YOUR DAY, SWEETHEART?

27:23.725 --> 27:24.851
UNEVENTFUL.

27:24.893 --> 27:27.354
REALLY?

27:24.893 --> 27:27.354
SOMETHING BOTHERING YOU?

27:27.396 --> 27:28.688
[ SCOFFS ]

27:28.730 --> 27:31.858
IT'S THE RAIN.

27:28.730 --> 27:31.858
REMINDS ME OF LONDON.

27:31.900 --> 27:34.194
LITTLE HOMESICK MAYBE.

27:34.236 --> 27:36.738
WE'LL HAVE TO WORK ON THAT.

27:40.117 --> 27:42.453
[ DIALING ]

27:53.922 --> 27:55.508
[ American accent ] EXCUSE ME.

27:55.549 --> 27:56.716
ARE YOU THE BRANCH MANAGER?

27:56.758 --> 27:58.051
YES. I'LL BE WITH YOU

27:56.758 --> 27:58.051
IN JUST ONE MOMENT.

27:58.093 --> 27:59.553
I'M AFRAID THIS CAN'T WAIT.

27:59.595 --> 28:01.388
CAN WE SPEAK TO YOU IN PRIVATE?

28:01.430 --> 28:02.640
OF COURSE.

28:02.680 --> 28:04.224
-PLEASE EXCUSE US FOR A MOMENT.

28:02.680 --> 28:04.224
-YES, SIR.

28:04.266 --> 28:05.476
WHAT SEEMS TO BE THE PROBLEM?

28:05.518 --> 28:07.311
THE "PROBLEM"

28:05.518 --> 28:07.311
IS THAT YOUR BANK JUST FAILED

28:07.353 --> 28:08.770
A PRELIMINARY STRESS TEST.

28:08.812 --> 28:11.815
ON A SCALE OF 1 TO 5 --

28:08.812 --> 28:11.815
1 BEING BEST, 5 BEING WORST --

28:11.857 --> 28:13.484
YOUR BANK SCORED...

28:13.526 --> 28:15.235
RISK MANAGEMENT, 5.

28:15.277 --> 28:16.487
DELINQUENT LOANS, 5.

28:16.529 --> 28:18.113
CASH RESERVES, 5.

28:18.155 --> 28:19.781
SO WE'RE GONNA NEED TO

28:18.155 --> 28:19.781
SEE EVERYTHING --

28:19.823 --> 28:22.284
THE BACK OFFICE,

28:19.823 --> 28:22.284
THE VAULT, EVERYTHING.

28:22.326 --> 28:24.578
THIS IS OUTRAGEOUS.

28:22.326 --> 28:24.578
WHY WASN'T I INFORMED?

28:24.620 --> 28:26.455
GO AHEAD AND CALL D.C.

28:24.620 --> 28:26.455
CHECK UP ON US.

28:26.497 --> 28:27.956
BUT I'D ADVISE YOU

28:26.497 --> 28:27.956
TO KEEP YOUR VOICE LOW

28:27.998 --> 28:29.583
UNLESS YOU WANT A RUN

28:27.998 --> 28:29.583
ON YOUR BROKE-ASS BANK.

28:29.625 --> 28:30.792
JUST SAYING.

28:32.503 --> 28:34.296
[ CELLPHONE RINGS, BEEP ]

28:34.338 --> 28:37.424
YEAH, THIS IS...MARCUS DUPREE.

28:37.466 --> 28:39.426
YES, THIS IS THE FDIC

28:37.466 --> 28:39.426
INVESTIGATION BUREAU.

28:39.468 --> 28:41.595
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

28:41.637 --> 28:43.763
I CAN CONFIRM

28:41.637 --> 28:43.763
THAT THERE IS A SPOT INSPECTION

28:43.805 --> 28:46.099
SCHEDULED FOR TODAY.

28:46.141 --> 28:48.060
THAT'S R--

28:46.141 --> 28:48.060
I GOT TO PUT YOU ON HOLD.

28:48.101 --> 28:49.562
RANDAL.

28:49.603 --> 28:50.812
[ SIGHS ]

28:50.854 --> 28:52.064
SINGAPORE, RIGHT?

28:52.105 --> 28:53.148
YEAH.

28:53.190 --> 28:55.108
PAUL McCARTNEY'S

28:53.190 --> 28:55.108
HOFNER BASS GUITAR.

28:55.150 --> 28:57.611
YOU OWE ME $27,000.

28:57.653 --> 29:00.113
OR WE CAN SPLIT THIS FEE

29:00.155 --> 29:01.865
AND WALK AWAY

29:00.155 --> 29:01.865
WITH $5 MILLION EACH.

29:01.907 --> 29:03.534
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

29:03.576 --> 29:05.327
YOU SHOULD HAVE PAID ME, RANDAL.

29:06.412 --> 29:10.290
[ Muzak playing ]

29:10.332 --> 29:12.334
[ Eliot and Randal grunting ]

29:17.548 --> 29:20.467
[ SIGHS ]

29:17.548 --> 29:20.467
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

29:20.509 --> 29:22.802
WHY COULDN'T YOU AND

29:20.509 --> 29:22.802
DOROTHY JUST RUN AWAY IN

29:20.509 --> 29:22.802
THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT?

29:22.844 --> 29:26.098
IN WHOSE CAR?

29:22.844 --> 29:26.098
HER FATHER'S?

29:26.139 --> 29:28.767
WE'D NEVER MAKE IT

29:26.139 --> 29:28.767
TO THE COUNTY LINE.

29:28.808 --> 29:31.103
WE HAD TO SLIP AWAY

29:28.808 --> 29:31.103
WHEN EVERYONE IN TOWN

29:31.144 --> 29:33.813
WAS WATCHING SOMETHING ELSE.

29:35.982 --> 29:38.277
YOU'RE NOT NERVOUS, ARE YOU?

29:38.318 --> 29:40.946
YOU CAN PLAY THIS PIECE

29:38.318 --> 29:40.946
IN YOUR SLEEP.

29:40.987 --> 29:43.449
YES. IT'S JUST...

29:43.490 --> 29:45.284
THERE ARE SO MANY PEOPLE

29:43.490 --> 29:45.284
HERE TONIGHT.

29:45.325 --> 29:48.120
OH, HONEY.

29:45.325 --> 29:48.120
YOU'RE GONNA BE WONDERFUL.

29:48.161 --> 29:49.162
AS ALWAYS.

29:49.204 --> 29:51.457
I BETTER GO PRACTICE.

29:51.498 --> 29:53.667
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

29:59.965 --> 30:01.592
ANY SIGN OF HIM?

30:01.634 --> 30:02.760
NO, SIR.

30:02.801 --> 30:04.595
ARE YOU SURE HE'S BACK?

30:04.637 --> 30:07.765
OH, HE'S HERE.

30:07.806 --> 30:09.349
YOU FIND HIM.

30:13.562 --> 30:16.398
[ TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS ]

30:27.993 --> 30:29.953
[ APPLAUSE ]

30:29.995 --> 30:33.624
[ ORGAN PLAYING WALTZ MUSIC ]

30:45.678 --> 30:49.931
[ APPLAUSE ]

30:51.642 --> 30:53.310
[ MUSIC CONTINUES ]

30:59.941 --> 31:01.943
[ APPLAUSE ]

31:06.281 --> 31:08.116
[ TWIG SNAPS ]

31:06.281 --> 31:08.116
DOROTHY.

31:09.075 --> 31:11.453
CHARLIE LAWSON.

31:13.497 --> 31:16.834
I THINK WE NEED TO HAVE A TALK.

31:22.172 --> 31:26.301
WHEN I SAW DOROTHY'S FATHER,

31:22.172 --> 31:26.301
I-I FIGURED...

31:26.343 --> 31:28.846
MY TICKET WAS PUNCHED.

31:28.887 --> 31:30.848
YOU'RE JUST BACK FROM THE WAR.

31:30.889 --> 31:32.516
EUROPE OR THE PACIFIC?

31:32.558 --> 31:34.685
FRANCE.

31:34.727 --> 31:37.020
WE LANDED IN CALAIS AFTER D-DAY.

31:37.062 --> 31:39.857
MY SWEET LORD.

31:39.939 --> 31:42.526
WE DO OWE YOU A DEBT.

31:42.568 --> 31:44.069
YOUR MOTHER SHOULD BE PROUD.

31:44.110 --> 31:48.281
DON'T YOU TALK ABOUT MY MOTHER.

31:44.110 --> 31:48.281
SHE'S NO FRIEND OF YOURS.

31:48.323 --> 31:49.783
NOW, HERE'S THE THING.

31:49.825 --> 31:54.120
JUST BECAUSE YOU SERVED

31:49.825 --> 31:54.120
OUR NATION HONORABLY

31:54.162 --> 31:58.417
DOESN'T GIVE YOU THE RIGHT

31:54.162 --> 31:58.417
TO SPEAK TO ME LIKE THAT.

31:58.458 --> 32:02.755
IT SEEMS TO ME YOU MIGHT HAVE

31:58.458 --> 32:02.755
FORGOTTEN YOUR PLACE.

32:02.796 --> 32:04.923
[ CHUCKLES, SNIFFS ]

32:04.964 --> 32:06.925
[ OWL HOOTS ]

32:06.966 --> 32:09.928
YOU WANT TO BEAT ME...

32:09.969 --> 32:11.597
GO AHEAD.

32:11.638 --> 32:14.099
NAH. [ SNIFFS ]

32:14.140 --> 32:15.768
I DON'T WANT TO DO THAT.

32:15.809 --> 32:19.104
I JUST WANT TO ASK YOU

32:15.809 --> 32:19.104
ONE QUESTION.

32:19.145 --> 32:21.690
WHAT ARE YOUR PLANS

32:19.145 --> 32:21.690
WITH MY DAUGHTER?

32:29.155 --> 32:30.282
[ RATTLING ]

32:30.323 --> 32:33.452
IT'S LOCKED FROM THE OUTSIDE.

32:33.493 --> 32:36.288
I HAVE TO GET OUT.

32:33.493 --> 32:36.288
I HAVE TO!

32:36.329 --> 32:39.124
WHATEVER IT IS THAT YOU AND MY

32:36.329 --> 32:39.124
WIFE ARE UP TO, IT STOPS NOW.

32:39.165 --> 32:40.959
NOW, I SAW CHARLIE HERE

32:39.165 --> 32:40.959
YESTERDAY.

32:41.000 --> 32:42.127
YOU TOLD MY FATHER?

32:42.168 --> 32:43.879
I WOULD NEVER DO THAT.

32:43.921 --> 32:45.714
BUT YOU GOT NO BUSINESS

32:43.921 --> 32:45.714
DRAGGING MY WIFE INTO THIS!

32:45.756 --> 32:47.966
-THIS IS MY TOWN!

32:45.756 --> 32:47.966
-YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND.

32:48.007 --> 32:49.968
IF MY FATHER FINDS CHARLIE --

32:50.009 --> 32:52.721
I HAVE TO GET OUT THERE!

32:50.009 --> 32:52.721
PLEASE!

32:52.763 --> 32:54.681
HMM?

32:54.723 --> 32:56.767
[ SMACKS LIPS ]

33:03.231 --> 33:06.234
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT!

33:03.231 --> 33:06.234
WAIT! WAIT!

33:07.903 --> 33:11.364
DOROTHY AND I

33:07.903 --> 33:11.364
WERE GOING TO CANADA.

33:11.406 --> 33:14.367
SHE SWIPED YOUR KEYS.

33:11.406 --> 33:14.367
WE WERE GONNA TAKE YOUR CAR.

33:14.409 --> 33:16.745
THEY'RE RIGHT THERE IN MY BAG.

33:21.040 --> 33:23.168
WHAT?

33:23.209 --> 33:24.503
GRENADE!

33:24.544 --> 33:26.797
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

33:28.674 --> 33:31.551
[ TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS ]

33:35.263 --> 33:38.475
I NEED ANOTHER PINEAPPLE.

33:35.263 --> 33:38.475
THIS IS FROM THAT BATCH OF DUDS.

33:41.561 --> 33:43.229
[ TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS ]

33:43.271 --> 33:45.440
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

34:00.121 --> 34:01.289
HEY! HEY!

34:00.121 --> 34:01.289
THERE THEY ARE!

34:06.211 --> 34:07.629
-OH! GET OUT OF HERE!

34:06.211 --> 34:07.629
-GO!

34:20.225 --> 34:22.019
OKAY, WE CAN JUMP OFF

34:20.225 --> 34:22.019
IN EDMUNDVILLE,

34:22.060 --> 34:23.854
CATCH THE WESTBOUND.

34:23.896 --> 34:25.188
YOUR FATHER WON'T CATCH US.

34:25.230 --> 34:28.692
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

34:25.230 --> 34:28.692
YOU KNOW THAT'S NOT TRUE.

34:28.734 --> 34:32.029
MY FATHER WILL DO

34:28.734 --> 34:32.029
WHATEVER IT TAKES

34:32.070 --> 34:34.197
TO FIND US

34:32.070 --> 34:34.197
AND BRING ME BACK HERE.

34:34.239 --> 34:37.325
-HE'LL HURT YOU.

34:34.239 --> 34:37.325
I CAN'T LET THAT HAPPEN.

34:34.239 --> 34:37.325
-I CAN --

34:37.367 --> 34:39.452
I CAN TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

34:39.494 --> 34:42.330
I KNOW YOU CAN.

34:39.494 --> 34:42.330
BUT I CAN'T.

34:44.207 --> 34:48.003
I'VE NEVER BEEN TO FRANCE,

34:44.207 --> 34:48.003
CHARLIE.

34:48.045 --> 34:50.881
THIS TOWN, THIS PLACE --

34:50.923 --> 34:53.926
IT'S MY HOME.

34:55.552 --> 34:58.179
HERE.

34:58.221 --> 34:59.472
WHAT?

34:59.514 --> 35:01.140
NO!

35:01.182 --> 35:03.643
NO, KEEP IT SAFE.

35:01.182 --> 35:03.643
KEEP IT SAFE FOR ME.

35:03.685 --> 35:06.187
KEEP IT SAFE.

35:11.777 --> 35:15.113
I LOVE YOU, DOROTHY.

35:16.489 --> 35:19.158
SO BEAUTIFUL.

35:21.494 --> 35:22.829
I LOVE YOU.

35:35.216 --> 35:37.385
[ SOBBING ]

35:43.683 --> 35:45.685
[ TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS ]

35:50.023 --> 35:52.651
AND...

35:52.692 --> 35:56.154
THAT WAS THE LAST TIME

35:52.692 --> 35:56.154
I SAW DOROTHY ROSS.

35:56.195 --> 35:57.990
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

35:58.031 --> 35:59.324
[ SNIFFLES ]

35:59.365 --> 36:01.367
BUT THE PAINTING --

35:59.365 --> 36:01.367
YOU GAVE IT BACK TO HER.

36:01.409 --> 36:03.870
I MEAN, YOU COULD HAVE BEEN SET

36:01.409 --> 36:03.870
FOR LIFE.

36:03.912 --> 36:05.538
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:05.580 --> 36:08.333
YEAH, SEEMS LIKE I READ THAT

36:05.580 --> 36:08.333
IN A LETTER BEFORE.

36:08.374 --> 36:10.836
DIDN'T WORK TOO WELL FOR HIM.

36:10.877 --> 36:12.045
HMM.

36:12.087 --> 36:13.964
MAYBE THE PAINTING'S A CURSE.

36:14.006 --> 36:16.466
SO YOU DIDN'T COME BACK TO TOWN

36:14.006 --> 36:16.466
FOR THE PAINTING.

36:16.508 --> 36:19.594
I GOT TO FRANCE ON MY OWN.

36:19.636 --> 36:25.142
I EVEN WALKED THE SAME ROAD

36:19.636 --> 36:25.142
AS VAN GOGH DID IN THE PAINTING.

36:27.727 --> 36:29.729
I'VE HAD A REMARKABLE LIFE.

36:31.982 --> 36:36.319
I CAME BACK TO THIS TOWN

36:31.982 --> 36:36.319
TO SEE HER.

36:37.988 --> 36:42.951
AND I WAS JUST

36:37.988 --> 36:42.951
A COUPLE OF YEARS TOO LATE.

36:42.993 --> 36:45.244
WHERE DO YOU THINK

36:42.993 --> 36:45.244
THE PAINTING IS NOW?

36:46.287 --> 36:49.290
DOES IT MATTER?

36:53.670 --> 36:57.465
WELL, WE COUNT AROUND $70,000

36:53.670 --> 36:57.465
IN SMALL BILLS.

36:57.507 --> 37:00.093
I TOLD YOU.

36:57.507 --> 37:00.093
DOROTHY DID SELL THAT PAINTING.

37:00.135 --> 37:01.845
THIS MUST BE ALL THAT WAS LEFT.

37:01.887 --> 37:03.680
I KNOW WHERE THE PAINTING IS.

37:03.722 --> 37:05.015
SOPHIE, HARDISON,

37:03.722 --> 37:05.015
PROTECT CHARLIE.

37:05.057 --> 37:07.475
ELIOT, COME WITH ME.

37:05.057 --> 37:07.475
I'LL SEND YOU THE ADDRESS.

37:14.566 --> 37:16.068
SIR, WE'RE CLOSED.

37:16.109 --> 37:19.029
WITH THE HISTORICAL SOCIETY.

37:16.109 --> 37:19.029
HERE TO FIX THE OLD WURLITZER.

37:20.739 --> 37:22.741
[ ORGAN PLAYING SCALES ]

37:27.662 --> 37:28.955
[ DISSONANT NOTE PLAYS ]

37:28.997 --> 37:30.832
[ DISSONANT NOTE PLAYS ]

37:30.874 --> 37:32.291
[ DISSONANT NOTE PLAYS ]

37:30.874 --> 37:32.291
HOW LONG THAT ONE BEEN OUT?

37:32.333 --> 37:33.793
OH, AS LONG AS I CAN REMEMBER.

37:33.835 --> 37:36.254
THE LADY WHO USED TO PLAY IT

37:33.835 --> 37:36.254
JUST FIGURED WAYS AROUND IT.

37:36.295 --> 37:38.631
-[ CHUCKLES ]

37:36.295 --> 37:38.631
-HMM.

37:58.693 --> 38:00.528
[ PIPE CLANGS ]

38:11.790 --> 38:13.750
[ GUN COCKS ]

38:11.790 --> 38:13.750
I'LL TAKE THAT NOW.

38:13.792 --> 38:17.087
OWEN.

38:17.129 --> 38:18.630
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

38:18.671 --> 38:22.134
I'VE SPENT THE LAST 20 YEARS

38:18.671 --> 38:22.134
OF MY LIFE CHASING A GHOST.

38:22.175 --> 38:23.802
LOST MY FAMILY.

38:23.843 --> 38:25.971
LOST EVERYTHING.

38:26.012 --> 38:28.431
I'M NOT LEAVING HERE WITHOUT IT.

38:28.473 --> 38:31.601
YOU KNOW, CHARLIE LAWSON SAID

38:28.473 --> 38:31.601
THIS PAINTING WAS CURSED.

38:31.643 --> 38:33.979
A GERMAN SOLDIER DIED FOR IT.

38:34.020 --> 38:36.355
LOOK WHAT IT'S DONE

38:34.020 --> 38:36.355
TO YOU, OWEN.

38:36.397 --> 38:39.358
NATE, I KNOW YOU THINK

38:36.397 --> 38:39.358
YOU CAN TALK ME OUT OF THIS.

38:39.400 --> 38:41.236
BUT YOU CAN'T.

38:41.278 --> 38:43.488
WELL, YOU KNOW, I'M NOT TRYING

38:41.278 --> 38:43.488
TO REASON WITH YOU, OWEN.

38:43.529 --> 38:45.698
I JUST WANT YOU TO UNDERSTAND

38:43.529 --> 38:45.698
WHY IT IS I'M DOING THIS.

38:48.910 --> 38:51.037
OH, NO!

38:48.910 --> 38:51.037
[ BLOWING SHARPLY ]

38:51.997 --> 38:56.293
[ CLANGING ]

38:57.877 --> 38:59.545
[ CLANG ]

39:00.922 --> 39:02.548
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

39:02.590 --> 39:05.093
[ GASPING ]

39:06.552 --> 39:09.181
THIS PAINTING'S ABOUT

39:06.552 --> 39:09.181
A MAN GOING TO WORK.

39:09.222 --> 39:12.433
THAT'S WHY YOU LOVED IT.

39:12.475 --> 39:15.312
SOMEHOW THAT GOT LOST.

39:25.322 --> 39:26.948
I THINK

39:25.322 --> 39:26.948
THE BOSTON MUSEUM OF ART

39:26.990 --> 39:28.950
IS AN EXCELLENT CHOICE, CHARLIE.

39:28.992 --> 39:30.785
HMM.

39:30.827 --> 39:32.370
H-HOW DID YOU FIGURE IT OUT?

39:32.411 --> 39:33.955
YOU TOLD ME.

39:35.456 --> 39:38.417
SEE, ONCE I KNEW THAT DOROTHY

39:35.456 --> 39:38.417
HAD THE PAINTING,

39:38.459 --> 39:41.379
THE KEY TO FINDING IT

39:38.459 --> 39:41.379
WAS UNDERSTANDING  HER.

39:41.420 --> 39:43.882
MY MOM PLAYED THE WURLITZER

39:41.420 --> 39:43.882
AT THE ROLLER PALACE

39:43.923 --> 39:45.175
FOR 50 YEARS.

39:45.217 --> 39:47.719
AND ANYTIME SOMEONE

39:45.217 --> 39:47.719
WOULD TRY TO TEAR IT DOWN,

39:47.760 --> 39:49.512
SHE WOULD FIGHT THEM

39:47.760 --> 39:49.512
TOOTH AND NAIL.

39:49.554 --> 39:50.889
NOW, SHE WAS LOYAL.

39:50.930 --> 39:53.683
LOYAL TO THIS TOWN,

39:50.930 --> 39:53.683
LOYAL TO YOU.

39:53.725 --> 39:54.976
SHE MADE YOU A PROMISE.

39:55.018 --> 39:57.145
SHE SAID THAT SHE WOULD KEEP

39:55.018 --> 39:57.145
THE VAN GOGH SAFE,

39:57.187 --> 39:59.314
AND THAT'S EXACTLY

39:57.187 --> 39:59.314
WHAT SHE DID...

39:59.356 --> 40:02.483
[ ORGAN PLAYING ]

40:02.525 --> 40:07.530
...WATCHING OVER IT EVERY TIME

40:02.525 --> 40:07.530
SHE PLAYED THE ORGAN.

40:13.578 --> 40:16.706
SHE SAVED HER TIPS

40:13.578 --> 40:16.706
ALL THOSE YEARS, HOPING.

40:16.748 --> 40:19.209
-IN CASE I CAME BACK.

40:16.748 --> 40:19.209
-YEAH.

40:22.087 --> 40:25.548
YOU KNOW...

40:25.590 --> 40:27.884
WHEN I CAME BACK HERE

40:25.590 --> 40:27.884
AND FOUND OUT SHE WAS GONE,

40:27.926 --> 40:31.554
I FELT CHEATED.

40:31.596 --> 40:37.560
I-I DIDN'T KNOW HOW SHE WOULD

40:31.596 --> 40:37.560
HAVE FELT ABOUT SEEING ME.

40:37.602 --> 40:41.147
NOW I-I GUESS I DO.

40:47.362 --> 40:49.989
YOU CAN'T POSSIBLY KNOW

40:47.362 --> 40:49.989
THAT'S THE REAL STORY.

40:50.031 --> 40:52.867
NO, BUT IT'S THE BEST STORY.

40:55.328 --> 40:57.330
[ SNEEZES ]

40:59.416 --> 41:02.877
AH.

40:59.416 --> 41:02.877
I GUESS THIS IS IT.

41:02.919 --> 41:04.879
YEAH.

41:02.919 --> 41:04.879
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

41:04.921 --> 41:08.549
THEY'RE GONNA BE DISCHARGING YOU

41:04.921 --> 41:08.549
IN ABOUT AN HOUR, SO...

41:08.591 --> 41:10.427
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF, CHARLIE.

41:10.468 --> 41:12.429
IT'S THE ONE THING

41:10.468 --> 41:12.429
I'VE ALWAYS DONE.

41:12.470 --> 41:14.097
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

41:14.139 --> 41:16.099
OKAY.

41:16.141 --> 41:19.477
THERE'S ONE THING

41:16.141 --> 41:19.477
I WANT TO TELL YOU.

41:22.147 --> 41:24.441
DON'T WASTE TIME.

41:24.523 --> 41:26.776
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:26.818 --> 41:27.860
YEAH.

41:36.202 --> 41:39.205
[ CHUCKLES ]
